1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
字幕转制｜天外生物
感谢原字幕制作者

2
00:00:22,650 --> 00:00:25,750
领衔主演
西尔维娅·克里斯蒂

3
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:29,500
导演
贾斯特·杰克金

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,800
查泰菜夫人的情人

5
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:37,500
主演
尼古拉斯·克莱

6
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,200
谢恩·布赖恩特

7
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:44,800
安·米切尔

8
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:48,500
伊丽莎白·斯普里格斯

9
00:01:15,820 --> 00:01:18,200
快点，安东，我要和你比赛，跑啊！
Come on, Anton, I'll race you. Get up!

10
00:01:56,950 --> 00:02:01,450
- 看，他们来了  - 咱们去告诉大家
- Look, they're coming.  - Let's go and tell everyone.

11
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:11,710
- 康妮，我赢了  - 我就知道你会赢
- Connie, I won.  - I knew you would.

12
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:18,590
- 你永远赢不了我  - 这次赌什么？
- you'll never beat me, as usual.  - What was the bet this time?

13
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:23,640
和新婚的查泰菜夫人跳第一个舞的荣幸
The honour of having the first dance with the new Lady Chatterley.

14
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,940
这位夫人很漂亮
This one's pretty enough...

15
00:02:48,990 --> 00:02:52,520
可我听说她是艺术家的女儿
...but I understand she's the daughter of an artist.

16
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:56,300
她正是克利福德和这所老宅子所需要的
She's just what Clifford and this old house needs.

17
00:02:56,550 --> 00:03:01,300
她有着别人永远无法拥有的活力
She's alive in the way the others never could be.

18
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:18,780
- 需求面前无法律，我的朋友  - 政治，都是政治
- Necessity knows no law, my friends.  - Politics, politics.

19
00:03:19,070 --> 00:03:24,620
- 要想毁掉聚会，就请德国人来  - 安东，咱们现在还不是敌人呢
- How to ruin a party: Invite a German.  - Anton, we're not enemies yet.

20
00:03:24,820 --> 00:03:29,080
- 可是形势很严峻  - 拜托，今晚别说这事
- But the situation is serious.  - Please, not this evening.

21
00:03:29,330 --> 00:03:35,290
- 为什么不和我妻子跳个舞？ - 荣幸至致，失陪一下
- Why don't you dance with my wife?  - With pleasure. Excuse me.

22
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:24,720
女士们，先生们，请大家注意啦
Ladies and gentlemen, may I have your attention, please?

23
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:31,810
非常抱歉打断大家跳舞，但我保证你们很愿意听到这个消息
I'm sorry to interrupt the dance, but I'm sure you'll want to hear the news.

24
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:36,730
在刚才的二十四分钟里，英国和德国已经处于交战状态
For the last 24 minutes, England has been at war with Germany.

25
00:04:40,650 --> 00:04:43,490
让我们国干杯
Let us drink to England.

26
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:49,120
英国
England.

27
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:53,330
- 英国  - 英国
- England.  - England.

28
00:04:53,790 --> 00:04:58,330
- 当然也为德国  - 为德国
- And to Germany, of course.  - To Germany.

29
00:04:58,580 --> 00:05:00,840
- 也为英国  - 为德国
- And to England.  - Germany.

30
00:05:03,380 --> 00:05:06,050
再见，姨妈，请照顾好康妮
Goodbye, Auntie. Look after Connie.

31
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:08,930
- 我很快就会回来  - 再见，希尔达
- I can't be long.  - Goodbye, Hilda.

32
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:12,680
再见，再见啦
Goodbye. Goodbye.

33
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:19,560
- 亲爱的，我不希望你去送我  - 真的吗？
- Darling, I'd rather you didn't come.  - Are you sure?

34
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:35,200
- 克里夫，多多保重  - 罗伯兹
- Cliff, take care of yourself.  - Roberts.

35
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,670
我应该能回来赶上猎野鸡的季节
Should be back just in time for the pheasant season.

36
00:05:49,010 --> 00:05:51,510
冲啊，弟兄们！
Come on, Iads!

37
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:57,100
冲啊！向前冲！
Go on! Forwards!

38
00:05:57,310 --> 00:06:02,820
快点！冲啊，快！
Faster! Go on, faster!

39
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:05,900
保持队形！保持队形！
Keep the line! Keep the line!

40
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:09,240
冲啊！向前冲！冲啊！
Forwards! Forwards, forwards!

41
00:06:09,490 --> 00:06:12,120
上，弟兄们！
Go on, Iads!

42
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:15,660
冲啊！
Forwards!

43
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:30,890
哥们，这人还有口气
This one's still breathing, Paddy.

44
00:08:14,610 --> 00:08:20,410
“你可以坐下，沃辛先生” 她在口袋里找着铅笔
"you can take a seat, Mr. Worthing." She looks in her pocket for a pencil.

45
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:23,960
“谢谢，布莱克奈夫人，我喜欢站着”
"Thank you, Lady Bracknell, I prefer standing."

46
00:08:24,210 --> 00:08:26,670
布菜克奈夫人手里拿着笔记本说
Lady Bracknell, notebook in hand:

47
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:30,840
“我这份合格者名单上没有你
"you are not down on my list of eligible young men...

48
00:08:31,090 --> 00:08:37,510
这和波尔顿女公爵的名单是一样的，我们一起做的
...but it's the same list the Duchess of Bolton has. We work together.

49
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:41,560
不过，如果你能回答一位慈爱母亲的问题
However, I will enter your name should your answers be...

50
00:08:41,770 --> 00:08:44,600
我就可以把你的名字加上”
...what an affectionate mother requires.

51
00:08:44,850 --> 00:08:49,610
“你抽烟吗？”“抽，必须承认，我抽烟”
Do you smoke?" "yes, I must admit, I smoke."

52
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:52,320
“很高兴听你这样说”
"I am glad to hear it."

53
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:56,860
十点半了，该睡觉了，亲爱的
10:30. It's time to go to bed, darling.

54
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:08,330
又是一天过去了
Dear, dear, another day gone.

55
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:31,690
谢谢，亲爱的，我自己来
Thank you, darling, I can manage.

56
00:10:09,060 --> 00:10:11,520
晚安，康妮
Good night, Connie.

57
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,340
早上好
Good morning.

58
00:10:42,260 --> 00:10:48,060
斯图尔特勋爵夫妇那美丽的家，弗里奇利大厦公开出售了
Fritchley Hall, the home of Lord and Lady Stewart is offered for sale.

59
00:10:48,310 --> 00:10:54,690
有传言说，马特洛克附近的西普利家可能会遭到同样命运
It's rumoured that Shipley, near Matlock, may suffer the same fate.

60
00:10:54,980 --> 00:10:58,440
好像整个世界都在我们周围崩溃
It's as if the whole world is collapsing around us.

61
00:10:58,690 --> 00:11:00,150
怎么回事，亲爱的？
What's that, darling?

62
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:04,950
他们要卖掉弗里奇利大厦和西普利家的房子
They want to sell Fritchley Hall and Shipley.

63
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:08,500
我看这样的事会一件接一件发生
I suppose the one thing pushes out the other.

64
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:12,460
咱们怎么样？咱们这房子呢？
But what about us? Here? This house?

65
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:16,250
除了变化本身，什么都在变
Everything changes except change itself.

66
00:11:57,750 --> 00:12:01,010
我想我要抽根雪茄
I fancy a cigar is called for.

67
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:05,180
我自己来，谢谢你，菲尔德．
I can manage. Thank you, Field.

68
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:11,230
- 今天晚上就到这了  - 好的，先生
- That will be all for this evening.  - Very good, sir.

69
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:18,320
我觉得你很了不起，真的
I think you're wonderful, I do, really.

70
00:12:18,570 --> 00:12:22,280
- 为什么？ - 你能这样陪着克利夫德
- Why?  - The way you are with Clifford.

71
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:27,120
我觉得这太了不起了，可怜的孩子…
I think it's wonderful, really. Poor boy...

72
00:12:27,370 --> 00:12:31,450
伤残成这样了
...so crippled as he is.

73
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:36,500
最多只能算半个男人，可以这么说
Not more than half a man, you might say.

74
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:40,000
对我这样的女人来说没什么
It's the right half for a woman like me.

75
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:44,430
他说话妙语连珠，机智诙谐
He can be so witty and entertaining.

76
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:49,810
不过对一位年轻的妻子那就不好说了
But for a young wife, I'm not so sure at all.

77
00:12:51,140 --> 00:12:56,900
- 要不要来一根？ - 谢谢，我自己有
- Care for one of mine?  - Thank you, I have one of my own.

78
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:59,820
我嫁给理查德时非常年轻
I was very young when I married Richard.

79
00:13:00,020 --> 00:13:04,610
我们想搞改革、搞政治，诸如此类，什么都想
We wanted reform, politics, all that sort of thing.

80
00:13:04,860 --> 00:13:09,450
我们也那样做了，可从他去世后，尽管有孩子们
And we got it. But ever since he died, despite the children...

81
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:14,250
我还是觉得活着毫无意义，这种感觉太可怕了
...I feel I've lived for nothing. It's a dreadful feeling.

82
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:20,040
知道自己来到世上要做的事，死的时候肯定完不成
To know you're bound to die without having the things you were born for.

83
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:25,510
死？谁要死？
Die? Who's going to die?

84
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:29,180
我死过又活了，所以我要说永生
I've been there and back. Immortality.

85
00:13:29,930 --> 00:13:36,560
我们来到世上为了什么？我觉得人生在世好像有很多事
What are we born for? It seems to me that we are born for so many things.

86
00:13:36,810 --> 00:13:40,480
又好像什么都没有
Or perhaps we're not born for anything at all.

87
00:13:40,730 --> 00:13:44,900
这只是我们下决心的问题
It's just a matter of making up our minds.

88
00:13:45,150 --> 00:13:47,950
- 为永生干杯  - 为永生
- Immortality.  - Immortality.

89
00:13:48,660 --> 00:13:53,240
我觉得女人应该经历更多的事
I think women should experiment more.

90
00:13:53,490 --> 00:13:56,330
得到你年轻时想要的一切
Get what you want in your youth.

91
00:13:56,540 --> 00:14:00,080
如果一个女人随着年华逝去，觉得自己虚度了光阴
Nothing is so bad for a woman getting on in years...

92
00:14:00,290 --> 00:14:03,460
还有什么比这更糟的
...than the thought that she's missed.

93
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:05,970
晚安，亲爱的
Good night, dear.

94
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:10,930
我明天一大早离开，所以见不到你了
I'm leaving early in the morning, so I can't see you again.

95
00:14:12,050 --> 00:14:16,730
没有什么能比一个被徒劳无益的悔恨
There's nothing so sad or futile...

96
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:21,770
纠缠着的老妇人更悲哀更无助的了
...as an elderly woman possessed by vain regrets.

97
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:26,840
我要疯了
I am possessed.

98
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:43,560
康妮，我得跟你谈谈
Connie, I need to talk to you.

99
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:46,440
坐一会儿吧
Sit down a moment.

100
00:15:50,490 --> 00:15:53,990
从某种意义上说，你是最悲惨的失败者
you know, you're the worst loser, in a sense.

101
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:58,240
- 亲爱的  - 我依赖你，靠你而活
- Darling.  - I depend on you, live on you.

102
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:01,250
而你放弃了生命中极为重要的部分
But you're denied a serious part of life.

103
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:06,670
你放弃的东西尝在你的潜意识中起作用，伤害你
The fact you are denied, it may work inside your subconscious, harming you.

104
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:11,720
可你知道我需要你就像你需要我一样
But you know I need you as much as you need me.

105
00:16:11,970 --> 00:16:17,140
- 以前你很需要我，对吗？ - 当然了
- you did want me before, didn't you?  - Of course.

106
00:16:17,390 --> 00:16:20,270
我知道，所以这才让人心酸
I know, and it's bitter.

107
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:25,690
我不想让你觉得你在为我牺牲
you see, I don't want you to feel you've brought me a sacrifice.

108
00:16:25,940 --> 00:16:29,860
康妮，我必须跟你说，如果有个男人
Connie, I must tell you this. If ever there's a man...

109
00:16:30,110 --> 00:16:34,530
你非常想让他和你做爱
...who you absolutely want to make love to you...

110
00:16:35,950 --> 00:16:41,290
那就接受他吧，如果你想，就找个情人吧
...take him. Have a lover if you want to.

111
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:46,920
快看，老鹰
Look, a kestrel.

112
00:16:50,550 --> 00:16:54,010
永远不要忘记，我爱你
Don't ever forget I love you.

113
00:16:58,260 --> 00:17:01,720
- 嗨，过来  - 过来，宝贝
- Hey, come on here.  - Come here, girl.

114
00:17:01,970 --> 00:17:05,060
过来，快过来
Come on up. Come on up.

115
00:17:07,020 --> 00:17:11,940
- 对不起，这狗打扰你们了  - 别担心，它是个好狗
- I'm sorry about the dog, sir.  - Don't worry, she's a good girl.

116
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:16,320
你能不能把我推回房子？
Look, will you give me a push back to the house?

117
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:24,080
- 你好，夫人  - 你好
- Milady.  - Hello.

118
00:17:24,330 --> 00:17:26,750
好了，拉吧
All right, pull.

119
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:52,610
谢谢，迈勒斯
Thank you, Mellors.

120
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:10,960
谢谢，菲尔德
Thank you, Field.

121
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:15,340
克利夫德？
Clifford?

122
00:18:16,170 --> 00:18:18,880
要帮忙吗？
Do you need some help?

123
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:24,310
- 不用，马上就好了  - 咱们去年情况怎么样？
- No, nearly done now.  - How did we do last year?

124
00:18:25,850 --> 00:18:30,770
还可以，连鸡都卖得不错
Not bad, considering. Even the pheasants sold quite well.

125
00:18:30,980 --> 00:18:34,780
那煤矿呢？是不是应该重新开张？
What about the mine? Shouldn't you open it again?

126
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:37,900
- 我听说现在煤…  - 还不是时候
- I heard that coal...  - Not the right time.

127
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:40,990
现在时机不好
Not the right time at all.

128
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:54,960
康妮
Connie.

129
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:03,300
没事，亲爱的，别着急
It's all right, darling. Don't worry.

130
00:19:23,410 --> 00:19:26,910
我烦透了这些唱片，亲爱的
I'm sick and tired of these records, darling.

131
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:31,500
- 能不能像往常那样为我弹点什么？ - 你想要我弹什么？
- Could you play me something?  - What would you like me to play?

132
00:19:31,960 --> 00:19:36,300
喜欢什么弹什么，你知道有首曲子你弹得特别好
Whatever you like. you know the one. The one you play so well.

133
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:38,960
那好吧
All right, then.

134
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,290
克利夫德！
Clifford!

135
00:20:14,460 --> 00:20:17,130
快去叫克里斯蒂医生
Call for Dr. Christie.

136
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:25,340
医生马上就来了
The doctor's on his way.

137
00:20:32,430 --> 00:20:34,650
他们来了，夫人
They're here, milady.

138
00:20:34,850 --> 00:20:37,980
不过不是医生，是护士
But it's not the doctor, it's a nurse.

139
00:20:46,570 --> 00:20:49,910
我是伯尔顿太太，听到消息马上就赶了过来
I'm Mrs. Bolton. I came as quickly as I could.

140
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:53,250
- 你的气色也不好  - 不，我没事
- you look ill too.  - No, I'm fine.

141
00:20:53,410 --> 00:20:58,960
一点都不好，我先给他看，然后再给你看
Far from fine. I'll take a look at him first, then I'll take a look at you.

142
00:20:59,670 --> 00:21:02,800
没事，我没事
I'm fine. I'm fine.

143
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:06,550
下午好，克利夫德先生
Good afternoon, Sir Clifford.

144
00:21:06,760 --> 00:21:09,100
伯尔顿太太，我什么事都没有
I'm perfectly all right.

145
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:13,890
如果不介意，让我看看再说吧，感觉怎么不好？
I'll decide, if you don't mind. What seems to be the trouble?

146
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:18,230
没什么新鲜的，还是老毛病
Nothing new, just the same old nonsense.

147
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:23,860
这回是肩膀，还是可恶的脊椎引起的
It's my shoulders this time, and what's left of my damned spine.

148
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:30,530
- 这天气真是拜上帝所赐  - 只要不发大水就好
- This weather is a godsend.  - Providing we don't get a flood.

149
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:33,450
不会的，不出这星期就会放晴
We won't. It'll clear up.

150
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:36,420
有什么我可以做的？
Isn't there anything I can do?

151
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:40,130
- 告诉我，如果再犯了我该怎么办？  - 好的
- Show me, in case it happens again.  - We'll see.

152
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:46,430
有你可做的事，去看看迈勒斯有没有让鸡孵蛋
you can do something. See if Mellors is setting eggs under the birds.

153
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:49,890
我们去年就孵了，希望今年做得更好
We did well last year. I want to do even better.

154
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:52,850
克利夫德，那事现在并不重要
Clifford, that's not important now.

155
00:21:53,060 --> 00:21:56,230
新鲜空气和健康的运动
Fresh air and healthy activity...

156
00:21:56,480 --> 00:22:00,560
是我给你开的药方，夫人
...that's my prescription for you, milady.

157
00:24:24,290 --> 00:24:26,380
疼痛没什么可怕的
