171
00:25:26,440 --> 00:25:30,480
- 什么这么好笑？ - 《哈吉巴巴历险记》
- Now, what's so funny?  - The Adventures of Hajji Baba.

172
00:25:31,070 --> 00:25:35,200
他厌恶不蒙面莎的英国女人
He's repelled by the naked faces of English women.

173
00:25:35,650 --> 00:25:38,110
如果她们蒙上脸
If only they'd covered their faces...

174
00:25:38,370 --> 00:25:41,830
那他身上将燃起怎样的激情
...what fire of passion would have run through him.

175
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:44,750
这太有趣了
That's amusing.

176
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:49,330
人们除了脸别的地方都看不见，也许是一种遗憾
It's a pity we never see anything of people but their face.

177
00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:54,550
毕竟对于大多数人来说，脸是最难看的
After all, the worst part of most people is their face.

178
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:58,930
你是说我们应该蒙着脸光着身子外出？
you mean if we covered our faces and walked about naked?

179
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:02,890
像雷诺阿那样，可以呀
Like Renoir. Why not?

180
00:26:06,270 --> 00:26:11,020
没有头的躯干部雕像往往非常漂亮
And a torso in sculpture is often so lovely without a head.

181
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:16,240
- 它有着自己的生命  - 也许吧
- It has a life of its own.  - Perhaps.

182
00:26:17,490 --> 00:26:21,240
