307
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:41,910
这不值得哭
It's not worth crying for.

308
00:41:56,720 --> 00:41:59,890
好啦，好啦
There, there.

309
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:02,140
没事啦
It's all right.

310
00:42:37,260 --> 00:42:39,470
你真漂亮
you're beautiful.

311
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:43,010
太美了
So beautiful.

312
00:45:10,990 --> 00:45:15,790
对不起，来晚了，为什么今天不让我来做呢？你可以走了
I'm sorry I'm late. Why don't I do that today? you're excused.

313
00:45:15,870 --> 00:45:18,710
- 很好，夫人  - 这主意好
- Very good, milady.  - What a nice idea.

314
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:21,090
想赛一盘吗？
Want a game in a minute?

315
00:45:22,210 --> 00:45:25,050
我不想再赢你了
I don't want to beat you again.

316
00:45:25,840 --> 00:45:29,640
今天你赢不了，我一直在练习
you won't today. I've been practising.

317
00:45:31,350 --> 00:45:34,100
- 别走，伯尔顿太太  - 有事吗，夫人？
- Don't go, Mrs. Bolton.  - Excuse me, milady.

318
00:45:34,730 --> 00:45:38,310
- 一起喝茶吧，你也是家里的一员  - 谢谢
- Join us, you're part of the family.  - Thank you.

319
00:45:38,480 --> 00:45:42,400
- 你喜欢什么样的茶？ - 很浓，加好多糖
- How do you like your tea?  - Very strong, lots of sugar.

320
00:45:42,610 --> 00:45:45,360
又浓又甜的茶
Strong, sweet tea.

321
00:45:45,530 --> 00:45:48,070
我的口味是从我丈夫那儿来的
I got the taste from my husband.

322
00:45:48,280 --> 00:45:51,950
- 他去世很多年了吗？ - 我当时二十四岁
- Is it many years since he died?  - I was 24.

323
00:45:52,160 --> 00:45:56,500
- 太可怕了  - 是啊，和你守寡的年纪一样，康妮
- How awful.  - yes, same age you were widowed, Con.

324
00:45:56,670 --> 00:46:01,210
我们正努力帮你站起来，不是吗？
Now, we're going to get you back on your feet, aren't we?

325
00:46:01,420 --> 00:46:04,760
- 是的  - 不知道你是怎么熬过来的
- yes.  - I don't know how you lived through it.

326
00:46:04,920 --> 00:46:06,550
我自己也没想到
I didn't think I could.

327
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:11,560
心起了很太作用，我怀念他，从来没有忘记他
The heart makes up for a lot. I miss him, but I'll never forget him.

328
00:46:11,720 --> 00:46:15,060
他从来没有离开我，我也决不会离开他
He'd never have left me, and I'll never leave him.

329
00:46:15,270 --> 00:46:18,020
这是给我们大家上的一课，康妮
A lesson to us all, Con.

330
00:46:21,690 --> 00:46:24,740
我是说，这非常感人，伯尔顿太太
I mean, that's very touching, Mrs. B.

331
00:46:26,150 --> 00:46:29,450
- 你永远不会离开我，对吧，康妮？ - 克利夫德
- you'll never leave me, will you?  - Clifford.

332
00:46:29,620 --> 00:46:34,580
一旦你在心里认为自己是妻子，那就永远是妻子
Once a wife in your heart, always a wife, I say.

333
00:46:38,790 --> 00:46:41,080
走啊，伯尔顿太太
Come on, Mrs. B.

334
00:46:41,290 --> 00:46:45,340
- 我的脑子都不转了  - 不想赢光我所有的钱啦？
- Can't think straight.  - Don't you want to win all my money?

335
00:46:45,550 --> 00:46:49,050
- 天太晚了  - 别埋怨
- It's late.  - Don't complain.

336
00:47:52,570 --> 00:47:54,200
将军
Check.

337
00:47:56,830 --> 00:47:58,540
太好了
Very good.

338
00:47:59,200 --> 00:48:04,210
天快亮了，你想睡的话，就去睡吧
It must be early light now. you can go to bed if you like.

339
00:48:04,380 --> 00:48:07,880
走之前把窗帘拉开，好吗？
Open the curtains before you leave, would you?

340
00:48:44,710 --> 00:48:47,840
- 你们把这些东西拿到哪儿去？ - 克利夫德先生吩咐
- Where are you taking this?  - Sir Clifford's instructions.

341
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:51,130
- “把它们埋藏到阁楼上”  - 他在哪儿呢？
- " Bury it in the attic," he said.  - Where is he?

342
00:48:51,340 --> 00:48:56,050
- 和两位先生在书房里  - 谢谢，菲尔德
- With two gentlemen in the library.  - Thank you, Field.

343
00:48:56,220 --> 00:49:01,180
我认为现在正是时机，但我们必须把设备现代化
Now is the right time, but we simply must have the bits modernised.

344
00:49:01,350 --> 00:49:07,190
特别是橡树林矿，因为我们可以最大限度地开采…
Especially the Oakwood Pit. We can exploit that to the last possibility...

345
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:11,610
- 早上好  - 各位，这是我妻子
- Good morning, everybody.  - Gentlemen, my wife.

346
00:49:13,280 --> 00:49:14,530
你好
How do you do?

347
00:49:14,740 --> 00:49:18,410
亲爱的，能不能让我们安安静静说会话？拜托！
Darling, would you let us talk in peace? Please!

348
00:49:18,870 --> 00:49:20,990
刚才说到哪儿了？
Now, where were we?

349
00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:24,250
坐下吧
Sit down.

350
00:50:04,120 --> 00:50:07,620
- 我做错什么了吗？ - 没有
- Have I done something wrong?  - No.

351
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:10,840
你觉得和我在一起贬低自己了吗？
you think you've lowered yourself with me?

352
00:50:11,040 --> 00:50:12,630
没有
No.

353
00:52:23,680 --> 00:52:26,600
使劲！好，另一侧
Push! Good. And the other side.

354
00:52:26,760 --> 00:52:28,560
使劲，使劲
And push, push.

355
00:52:28,770 --> 00:52:32,980
你必须让肩膀使劲，休息一下
you must strengthen these shoulders. And rest.

356
00:52:36,360 --> 00:52:41,070
- 你真的觉得有希望吗？ - 你相信我吗？
- Do you really think there's hope?  - Do you trust me?

357
00:52:42,240 --> 00:52:46,070
- 相信，伯尔顿太太  - 那好，咱们再来
- yes, Mrs. B.  - Well, then, try again.

358
00:52:47,830 --> 00:52:50,080
向上抬，使劲
Lift and push.

359
00:52:50,370 --> 00:52:52,250
好，就这样，好
Good, good, good.

360
00:52:52,460 --> 00:52:54,330
休息一下，好
And rest. Good.

361
00:52:55,960 --> 00:52:59,050
我觉得你好可爱
you're lovely to me.

362
00:52:59,210 --> 00:53:03,430
- 摸起来好舒服  - 不要哭
- So lovely to touch.  - Don't cry.

363
00:53:04,470 --> 00:53:06,760
我曾读过这样一段话
I read something one day:

364
00:53:10,970 --> 00:53:14,480
“我要经历人生中的一切
" I will experience everything in life...

365
00:53:14,940 --> 00:53:18,400
这样，当我走上通往死亡的最后旅程
...so on the final journey to my death...

366
00:53:19,150 --> 00:53:23,610
我的夜晚就不会被懊悔吞噬”
...the nights will not be haunted by regret."

367
00:53:31,120 --> 00:53:33,410
所以用不着哭
So no need to cry.

368
00:53:33,660 --> 00:53:37,420
别担心，这真的很幸福
Don't worry, it's really happiness.

369
00:53:48,390 --> 00:53:50,010
人都去哪儿了？
Where are the others?

370
00:53:50,220 --> 00:53:54,560
克利夫德先生在书房，不让别人打扰他
Sir Clifford is in the library and asked not to be disturbed.

371
00:53:54,770 --> 00:53:57,600
伯尔顿太太在午睡
Mrs. Bolton is taking a nap.

372
00:53:58,440 --> 00:54:02,860
- 那这是专门为我准备的了  - 是的，夫人
- Well, it will be just for me, then.  - yes, milady.

373
00:54:03,110 --> 00:54:05,360
这份杂志是你的
This magazine came for you.

374
00:54:45,570 --> 00:54:47,030
康妮
Connie.

375
00:54:49,320 --> 00:54:52,700
我亲爱的的康妮，你很开心吧？
My darling Connie. Are you happy?

376
00:54:52,990 --> 00:54:56,330
- 怎么了？ - 因为你的样子非常可爱
- Why?  - Because you look so adorable.

377
00:54:56,540 --> 00:54:59,540
如果你不开心，我会受不了的
I couldn't bear it if you were unhappy.

378
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:02,630
你太好心了
So kind.

379
00:55:02,790 --> 00:55:07,340
我真心认为我应该死去，他们应该让我死
I honestly think I should have died. They should have let me.

380
00:55:07,630 --> 00:55:14,260
克利夫德，别这样，如果某种东西失去了，那并不意味着全部失去
Clifford, don't. If something is lost, it needn't be all lost, need it?

381
00:55:14,510 --> 00:55:18,730
如果没人想要我活，那我就没有理由活下去
There's no reason for me to live if nobody wants me to live.

382
00:55:20,060 --> 00:55:22,360
刚才看见你在那里，我就想
Just seeing you there then...

383
00:55:22,440 --> 00:55:27,530
如果我死了，你就可以解脱了，可能你也清楚这点
...I thought you'd be better off if I were dead. Perhaps you knew it.

384
00:55:27,900 --> 00:55:30,410
我不想让你死
I don't want you to die...

385
00:55:30,610 --> 00:55:34,990
可如果让我为你的生死承担责任，那就太残酷了
...but it is cruel to make me responsible for your living.

386
00:55:38,160 --> 00:55:40,830
你自己想活，对不对？
you want to live, don't you?

387
00:55:41,540 --> 00:55:44,170
亲爱的，对不起
Darling, I'm sorry.

388
00:55:44,920 --> 00:55:47,300
我太无情了
I'm a real brute.

389
00:55:48,420 --> 00:55:51,260
别哭，别因为…
Don't cry. Don't...

390
00:55:51,800 --> 00:55:54,430
我的自私而哭，
...for my selfish sake.

391
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:57,100
我不值得你这样
I'm not worthy of you.

392
00:56:03,440 --> 00:56:05,730
在这儿等着’，迈勒斯
Wait here, Mellors.

393
00:56:09,030 --> 00:56:11,280
你来这儿干什么？
What are you doing here?

394
00:56:17,620 --> 00:56:20,080
迈勒斯，有什么事吗？
yes, Mellors, what is it?

395
00:56:20,290 --> 00:56:25,460
我今天早上抓到两个偷猎者，还带着夹子和野兔
I caught a couple of poachers, sir, with snares and rabbits, this morning.

396
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:29,380
- 他们在哪儿  - 在外面，先生
- Where are they?  - Outside, sir.

397
00:56:38,810 --> 00:56:41,560
我该怎么处置他们？
What should I do about them?

398
00:56:42,020 --> 00:56:44,310
- 起诉  - 是，先生
- Prosecute.  - yes, sir.

399
00:56:44,560 --> 00:56:47,650
有必要起诉吗？
Is it necessary to prosecute them?

400
00:56:47,820 --> 00:56:53,410
偷猎野兔有必要吗？干这种事有必要吗？
Is it necessary to poach rabbits? Or anything else for that matter?

401
00:56:54,950 --> 00:56:58,620
如果不起诉，满树林都是他们了
They'd be all over the wood if we didn't prosecute.

402
00:56:59,240 --> 00:57:02,250
- 你们以前都是矿工吧？ - 是的，夫人
- you were colliers, weren't you?  - yes, milady.

403
00:57:02,410 --> 00:57:05,790
你看，他们偷猎是因为饥饿…
you see, they're poaching because they're hungry...

404
00:57:05,960 --> 00:57:08,250
夫人阁下说得对
Her ladyship is right.

405
00:57:08,420 --> 00:57:11,340
我们不起诉了，放了他们
We won't prosecute. Let them go.

406
00:57:13,050 --> 00:57:16,140
- 不过要先打一顿  - 克利夫德！
- After you've thrashed them.  - Clifford!

407
00:57:23,520 --> 00:57:28,900
他要么打他们，要么结柬自己在这儿的工作
He'll thrash them, or he'll consider his employment here ended.

408
00:58:24,580 --> 00:58:25,830
过去
Go on.

409
00:58:26,040 --> 00:58:27,710
好！
Good!

410
00:58:48,600 --> 00:58:50,810
谢谢，迈勒斯
Thank you, Mellors.

411
00:58:58,280 --> 00:59:00,200
走吧
Come on, then.

412
00:59:35,400 --> 00:59:38,280
- 你迟到了  - 我故意的
- you're late.  - I meant to be.

413
00:59:38,490 --> 00:59:42,620
- 不是你想让我来的吗？ - 不是你自己想来才来的吗？
- Didn't you want me here?  - Is it only to be when you want?

414
00:59:42,820 --> 00:59:46,160
偷猎者的事你觉得无所谓吗？
What happened to those poachers didn't bother you?

415
00:59:46,370 --> 00:59:50,330
- 你好像无所谓呀  - 我能不服从命令吗？
- It didn't seem to bother you.  - Should I have disobeyed him?

416
00:59:50,500 --> 00:59:53,310
即使这样，你也会打他们的
you would have beaten them anyway.

417
00:59:53,350 --> 00:59:56,380
- 即便这样  - 你怎么了？夫人
- Even so.  - Even so, milady.

418
01:00:02,470 --> 01:00:04,850
好啦，对不起
Okay, I'm sorry.

419
01:00:11,520 --> 01:00:13,810
你现在够了
Good.

420
01:00:17,820 --> 01:00:21,950
今天快多了，再做两个
Faster today. A couple more.

421
01:00:26,620 --> 01:00:28,410
很好
That's good.

422
01:00:30,080 --> 01:00:33,080
说实话，刚开始的时候
To be honest, when we started...

423
01:00:33,290 --> 01:00:36,340
我没抱什么希望
...I thought it was hopeless.

424
01:00:37,170 --> 01:00:40,510
可现在我觉得你能行
But now I think you can do it.

425
01:00:41,840 --> 01:00:46,760
- 要是有了孩子怎么办？ - 我很愿意有孩子
- What happens if you have a child?  - I should like to have a child.

426
01:00:50,020 --> 01:00:52,390
那克利夫德先生呢？
What about Sir Clifford?

427
01:00:58,110 --> 01:01:01,530
克利夫德说过这事
Clifford talked about it.

428
01:01:01,740 --> 01:01:04,660
- 他想要子嗣  - 什么？
- He wants a son and heir.  - What?

429
01:01:06,570 --> 01:01:08,660
他知道我？
He knows about me?

430
01:01:08,870 --> 01:01:10,160
不
No.

431
01:01:10,500 --> 01:01:13,160
如果有了孩子，你会告诉他吗？
If you have a child, you'll tell him?

432
01:01:13,290 --> 01:01:16,960
如果他怀疑你，我就不得不离开
If he ever suspects about you, I'd have to go away.

433
01:01:17,210 --> 01:01:18,460
为什么？
What for?

434
01:01:21,880 --> 01:01:24,050
离开你我活不下去
I couldn't live without you...

435
01:01:24,260 --> 01:01:28,180
可如果他知道了你，我就无法和他生活下去
...but I couldn't live with him if he knew about you.

436
01:01:34,810 --> 01:01:38,730
如果你走了，再也见不到我了，你会焦虑不安吗？
Wouldn't fret if you went away and never saw me again?

437
01:01:38,900 --> 01:01:42,110
是的，我会在意，会焦虑不安
yes, I'd mind. I'd fret.

438
01:01:42,320 --> 01:01:46,660
- 你会在意吗？ - 是的，我会
- Should you mind?  - Aye, that I would.

439
01:01:55,250 --> 01:02:00,840
我想让要你骗一次人，去我的小屋过一夜，就一次
I should like you to lie one night with me at my cottage, just for once.

440
01:02:05,510 --> 01:02:07,470
我必须要走了
I must go now.

441
01:02:26,530 --> 01:02:28,740
对不起，夫人
Sorry, milady.

442
01:02:30,950 --> 01:02:33,620
- 克利夫德先生呢？  - 在书房
- Where's Sir Clifford?  - In the library.

443
01:02:33,870 --> 01:02:36,960
- 也许他没听见  - 我去告诉他
- Perhaps he didn't hear.  - I'll tell him.

444
01:02:37,210 --> 01:02:38,960
夫人
Milady.

445
01:03:07,700 --> 01:03:11,410
- 你不想吃晚餐吗？ - 想，我饿极了
- Aren't you coming in to dinner?  - yes, I'm starving.

446
01:03:11,660 --> 01:03:14,660
我只是想把这些计划做完
I just want to finish with these plans.

447
01:03:14,870 --> 01:03:17,540
什么计划？煤矿的？
What is it, the mine?

448
01:03:18,080 --> 01:03:22,000
我无法开创一个朝代，无法像雷诺阿那样画画
I can't father a dynasty. I can't paint like Renoir.

449
01:03:22,210 --> 01:03:24,250
但我可以做企业，康妮
It has to be business, Con.

450
01:03:24,460 --> 01:03:27,550
查泰莱家族的姓氏一定要永远流传
Immortality must be the name Chatterley.

451
01:03:27,760 --> 01:03:30,130
咱们就从煤矿开始
We start with the mine.

452
01:03:30,510 --> 01:03:32,970
你在听我说话吗？
Are you listening to me?

453
01:03:34,220 --> 01:03:37,980
咱们必须先在收入和资本方面做出牺牲
We'll have to make sacrifices in income and capital...

454
01:03:38,140 --> 01:03:40,310
因为我们要进行现代化改造
...because we must modernise it.

455
01:03:42,440 --> 01:03:44,860
晚安，克利夫德
Good night, Clifford.

456
01:03:48,490 --> 01:03:51,740
晚安，康妮，睡个好觉
Good night, Con. Sleep well.

457
01:04:14,850 --> 01:04:17,770
我真怕你今天不来了，
I was scared you wouldn't come today.

458
01:04:19,770 --> 01:04:22,600
你为什么要找我这样一个下等人？
What do you come to a fellow like me for?

459
01:04:22,770 --> 01:04:26,360
因为你可以想要就要，不想要就不要吗？
Because you can take it or leave it as you please?

460
01:04:26,570 --> 01:04:29,030
我见过你一次，当时你在洗澡
I saw you once, washing.

461
01:04:29,280 --> 01:04:33,030
- 我觉得你很美  - 我？
- I thought you were beautiful.  - Me?

462
01:04:33,740 --> 01:04:37,290
你的身体很美，我想要你
your body was beautiful. I wanted you.

463
01:04:37,540 --> 01:04:39,410
我的身体，很美？
My body, beautiful?

464
01:04:39,620 --> 01:04:42,830
是你觉得吧？跟那些上层美少年比吗？
To you? As knows all the tiptop young fellas?

465
01:04:43,000 --> 01:04:46,630
- 我说的不是漂亮  - 心灵美才是真美
- I don't mean handsome.  - Handsome is as handsome does.

466
01:04:46,840 --> 01:04:49,420
你对我并不认真，对吧？
you don't take me serious, do you?

467
01:04:49,590 --> 01:04:52,720
我在你面前是什么人？你们的人会怎么说？
What am I to you? What do your sort say?

468
01:04:52,970 --> 01:04:54,720
说我是“鸭”？
A fucker?

469
01:04:55,970 --> 01:04:58,260
不，是情人
No, lover.

470
01:04:58,640 --> 01:05:01,180
你是我的情人
you are my lover.

471
01:05:08,150 --> 01:05:11,240
你就是没结婚，也不会嫁给我
