641
01:33:37,440 --> 01:33:42,110
我喜欢在这儿，这让我左右为难的窘境显得更为英勇
I quite enjoy it here. It makes my dilemma seem even more heroic.

642
01:33:42,280 --> 01:33:46,910
左右为难？这儿有你一封信
Dilemma? This letter's arrived for you.

643
01:33:47,950 --> 01:33:51,080
希望是好消息
I hope that it's good news.

644
01:33:51,500 --> 01:33:54,210
咱们一会儿见
I'll see you in a minute.

645
01:34:21,730 --> 01:34:24,320
康妮，亲爱的，走啊
Connie, dear, come on.

646
01:34:24,530 --> 01:34:27,370
你不想游泳吗？
Don't you want to go swimming?

647
01:34:50,600 --> 01:34:53,180
说实话，康妮，你太让人扫兴了
Honestly, Connie, you're such a bore.

648
01:34:53,350 --> 01:34:56,520
克利夫德安排你远走国外
Clifford arranges it by sending you into exile...

649
01:34:56,690 --> 01:35:01,770
可大家都做的事，你偏不做
...and all you do is the exact opposite of what everyone else wants to do.

650
01:35:02,440 --> 01:35:05,240
怀孕的女人是可以胡思乱想的
Pregnant women are allowed their whims.

651
01:35:05,740 --> 01:35:10,570
- 你不可能怀孕  - 我怀孕了，刚看过医生
- you can't be pregnant.  - I am. I've seen a doctor.

652
01:35:11,990 --> 01:35:14,700
这太可怕了
Absolutely awful.

653
01:35:15,330 --> 01:35:18,670
可我觉得这是最好的喜事
It's the best thing that ever happened to me.

654
01:35:18,920 --> 01:35:21,000
别傻了
Don't be silly.

655
01:35:21,250 --> 01:35:26,170
- 我们该拿你和那个怎么办？  - 送我回英国
- What will we do with you and it?  - Get me back to England.

656
01:35:49,740 --> 01:35:53,280
- 克利夫德  - 等一下
- Clifford?  - Wait.

657
01:35:54,910 --> 01:35:57,540
- 欢迎回家，夫人  - 你好
- Welcome back, milady.  - Hello.

658
01:35:59,290 --> 01:36:04,750
这是不是奇迹？都是伯尔顿太太的功劳
Isn't it simply wonderful? And all Mrs. B's doing.

659
01:36:06,710 --> 01:36:11,640
我的鼓励，克利夫德先生，主要是你的意志力
My encouragement, perhaps, Sir Clifford, your will-power.

660
01:36:29,650 --> 01:36:33,120
当心！没事吧？
Be careful! Are you all right?

661
01:36:34,200 --> 01:36:38,370
真是费了大劲了，不过确实值得
It's the devil of an effort but really worth it.

662
01:36:38,620 --> 01:36:42,000
- 最袁的成就是下到了矿井里  - 什么？
- Going down the mine was the triumph.  - What?

663
01:36:42,170 --> 01:36:45,540
我在信上都写了，你没收到我的信吗？
I wrote you about it. Didn't you get my letters?

664
01:36:45,710 --> 01:36:48,340
我把所有事情都写信告诉你了
I wrote you about everything.

665
01:36:59,060 --> 01:37:00,850
奥利弗？
Oliver?

666
01:37:01,730 --> 01:37:05,900
夫人？哦，他已经不在这儿工作了
Milady? Oh, he don't work here no more.

667
01:37:06,070 --> 01:37:08,190
有什么重要的事吗？
Was it anything important?

668
01:37:08,440 --> 01:37:11,700
没有，谢谢，对不起打扰你了
No, thank you. I'm sorry to have troubled you.

669
01:37:24,790 --> 01:37:30,090
- 迈勒斯出什么事了？ - 他走了，克利夫德先生解雇了他
- What's happened to Mellors?  - He's gone. Sir Clifford dismissed him.

670
01:37:30,340 --> 01:37:32,130
明白了
I see.

671
01:37:32,970 --> 01:37:35,300
克利夫德，你最好把一切都告诉我
you'd better tell me everything.

672
01:37:35,510 --> 01:37:37,260
- 告诉什么？  - 迈勒斯的事
- About what?  - Mellors.

673
01:37:37,470 --> 01:37:39,430
迈勒斯？
Mellors?

674
01:37:40,140 --> 01:37:43,310
我给你的信上都写了
I wrote you about it. It was in my letters.

675
01:37:43,520 --> 01:37:46,270
你的信我没看，快告诉我
I didn't read your letters. Tell me.

676
01:37:46,480 --> 01:37:50,070
我还以为你因为那个原因不回信呢
I thought you didn't answer them, because of that.

677
01:37:50,280 --> 01:37:54,820
听说你要回来，我还以为你原谅了我
When I heard you were coming back, I thought you'd forgiven me.

678
01:37:55,030 --> 01:37:57,580
因为什么原因？
Because of what?

679
01:37:59,660 --> 01:38:01,330
他确实不想留在这儿
He didn't want to stay.

680
01:38:01,540 --> 01:38:06,380
你送走了我，解雇了他，我真不敢相信
you sent me away, and you dismissed him. I can't believe it.

681
01:38:06,540 --> 01:38:10,500
我不想让你太痴迷他
I didn't want you to become too fond of him.

682
01:38:11,340 --> 01:38:14,470
我知道我们达成过一致，你可以有情人
I know we agreed about you having a lover...

683
01:38:14,720 --> 01:38:19,260
但我这样做是因为你，是为了减轻你的痛苦
...but I did it because of you, to save you pain.

684
01:38:19,430 --> 01:38:22,520
毕竟我们讨论过子嗣的事
After all, we did talk about a son and heir...

685
01:38:22,730 --> 01:38:25,020
如果你见他的次数太多
...and if you'd saw too much of him...

686
01:38:25,230 --> 01:38:28,230
谁知道顶我姓氏的会是什么杂种
...who knows what bastards I'd give my name.

687
01:38:28,440 --> 01:38:32,990
- 你的姓氏  - 康妮，你清楚我的立场
- your name.  - Con, surely you understand my position.

688
01:38:33,190 --> 01:38:35,360
克利夫德，我怀孕了
Clifford, I'm pregnant.

689
01:38:35,610 --> 01:38:39,410
他是孩子的父亲，你的姓氏完了
He's the father, and your name be damned.

690
01:38:56,220 --> 01:39:00,850
告诉你吧，在煤矿外面干活越来越难了
I tell you, love, work outside the mine is getting hard to come by.

691
01:39:12,610 --> 01:39:15,650
- 你来这儿干什么？ - 我刚回来
- What are you doing here?  - I just got back.

692
01:39:15,820 --> 01:39:18,820
- 是吗？你想干什么？ - 拜托…
- Did you, now? What do you want?  - Please...

693
01:39:18,990 --> 01:39:23,120
听着，这一切已经不可能了，事情已经结束了
Look, it can't be the way it was, so there's an end to it.

694
01:39:23,290 --> 01:39:26,210
你不想再要我了吗？
But don't you want me anymore?

695
01:39:35,170 --> 01:39:38,090
我想和你在一起
I want to be with you.

696
01:39:39,340 --> 01:39:42,890
我不想在我的一生中没有你
I don't want to miss you all my life.

697
01:39:44,810 --> 01:39:49,190
如果你真恨我，为什么还要为查泰菜家干苦力？
If you hate me, how can you still slave for the Chatterleys?

698
01:39:49,440 --> 01:39:51,360
- 听说过加拿大吗？ - 什么？
- Have you heard of Canada?  - What?

699
01:39:51,610 --> 01:39:56,440
加拿大，每周十四镑工钱，我在为自己挣路费
Canada, 14 pounds a week. I'm working to earn my fare.

700
01:39:56,610 --> 01:40:00,200
- 听我说，我都计划好了  - 不
- Listen to me, I've got it all planned...  - No.

701
01:40:00,410 --> 01:40:03,330
你怎么会喜欢我这种人？
How can you like the likes of me?

702
01:40:04,870 --> 01:40:08,660
- 奥利弗，我怀孕了  - 他妈的
- Oliver, I'm pregnant.  - Damn you.

703
01:40:08,910 --> 01:40:12,500
你得到了你想要的，克利夫德先生得到了孩子
you got what you want, and Sir Clifford gets a child.

704
01:40:12,710 --> 01:40:16,090
不，孩子会姓我娘家姓，或是你的姓
No, it will have my maiden name or your name.

705
01:40:16,260 --> 01:40:20,300
不会再有姓查泰菜的人了，克利夫德是最后一个
There will be no other Chatterley. Clifford is the last.

706
01:40:20,470 --> 01:40:23,390
不管你和不和我在一起，我都会离开他
I'll leave him, whether you come or not.

707
01:40:23,640 --> 01:40:27,770
咱们去哪儿？咱们干什么？我能干什么？
And where will we go? What will we do? What will I do?

708
01:40:28,020 --> 01:40:31,060
你可以经营自己的农场
you could run your own farm.

709
01:40:31,440 --> 01:40:35,070
- 怎么经营？ - 可以用我的收入
- How?  - We could use my income.

710
01:40:37,110 --> 01:40:40,030
你看不到自己活得像个奴隶吗？
Can't you see you live like a slave?

711
01:40:40,200 --> 01:40:44,410
- 我让自己自由了，你也可以  - 我不做吃软饭的男人
- I've made myself free. you can too.  - I'll not be a kept man.

712
01:40:44,580 --> 01:40:49,410
我们的孩子，不属于哪个阶级，是你我最好部分的结合
And our child, no class. The best of you, the best of me.

713
01:40:49,620 --> 01:40:51,540
你还记得吗？
Do you remember?

714
01:40:51,790 --> 01:40:55,880
“我的夜晚就不会被懊悔吞噬”
"My nights will not be haunted by regrets."

715
01:41:03,390 --> 01:41:09,850
- 你真的觉得我很美？ - 你就是很美
- So you really think I'm beautiful?  - you are.

716
01:41:13,020 --> 01:41:15,900
- 还有多长时间？ - 七个月
- How long to go?  - Seven months.

717
01:41:16,110 --> 01:41:20,490
咱们等着吧，等着吧
We'll see, we'll see.

718
01:41:27,580 --> 01:41:29,240
康妮？
Connie?
